STM32Loader
===========

Python script which will talk to the STM32 bootloader to upload and download firmware.

Original Version by: Ivan A-R <ivan@tuxotronic.org>

Usage:
    stm32loader list
    stm32loader info COM3
    stm32loader write COM3 file.bin [--erase] [--verify] [--run] [--go-addr 0x08000000]
    stm32loader erase COM3 [--run] [--go-addr 0x08000000]
    stm32loader read COM3 dump.bin --length 0x1000

Options:
    --run              Release/reset the chip after the operation so it runs normally.
    --go-addr ADDR     Send the STM32 bootloader GO command to ADDR after the operation.
    --address ADDR     Target flash address (default: 0x08000000).
    --baud BAUD        Baud rate (default: 115200).

Example:
stm32loader write COM3 somefile.bin --erase --verify --run

This will pre-erase flash, write somefile.bin to the flash on the device, and then perform a verification after writing is finished.

If your board stays in the ROM bootloader unless it is hardware-reset with BOOT0 low, use --run.
If the MCU supports jumping directly from the bootloader, use --go-addr 0x08000000.
